--options (-o)		Prints available application options (i.e ZFS, LUKS)
--version (-v)		Prints author, version, license information
--help    (-h)		Prints this help page

Usage:
You can run the program directly by typing:

# ./createInit

or you can pass options to it. If you know the kernel and option you want,
you can pass it to the script directly like this:

# ./createInit 1 3.7.5-ALL
